According to the [[Office for National Statistics]], at the time of the [[United Kingdom Census 2001]], Chadderton (urban-core and sub-area) had a total resident population of 33,001.<ref>{{citation |title=Greater Manchester Urban Area |url=http://www.statistics.gov.uk/census2001/greater_manchester_urban_area.asp |publisher=statistics.gov.uk |accessdate=2008-07-29|author=Office for National Statistics|authorlink=Office for National Statistics|work=[[United Kingdom Census 2001]]}}</ref> The population density was {{convert|8669|PD/sqmi|0}}, with a 100 to 95.4 female-to-male ratio.<ref>{{citation |title=KS01 Usual resident population: Census 2001, Key Statistics for urban areas |publisher=statistics.gov.uk |url=http://www.statistics.gov.uk/statbase/ssdataset.asp?vlnk=8271&More=Y |date=2005-02-07|author=Office for National Statistics|authorlink=Office for National Statistics|work=[[United Kingdom Census 2001]]|accessdate=2008-09-20 }}</ref> Of those over 16 years old, 27.2&nbsp;per&nbsp;cent were single (never married) 44.5&nbsp;per&nbsp;cent married, and 8.5&nbsp;per&nbsp;cent divorced.<ref>{{citation |title=KS04 Marital status: Census 2001, Key Statistics for urban areas |publisher=statistics.gov.uk |url=http://www.statistics.gov.uk/statbase/ssdataset.asp?vlnk=8276&More=Y |date=2005-02-02|author=Office for National Statistics|authorlink=Office for National Statistics|work=[[United Kingdom Census 2001]]|accessdate=2008-08-31}}</ref> Chadderton's 13,698 households included 28.8&nbsp;per&nbsp;cent one-person, 38.7&nbsp;per&nbsp;cent married couples living together, 8.9&nbsp;per&nbsp;cent [[cohabitation|co-habiting]] couples, and 10.3&nbsp;per&nbsp;cent single parents with their children.<ref>{{citation |title=KS20 Household composition: Census 2001, Key Statistics for urban areas |publisher=statistics.gov.uk |url=http://www.statistics.gov.uk/statbase/ssdataset.asp?vlnk=8349&More=Y |date=2005-02-02|author=Office for National Statistics|authorlink=Office for National Statistics|work=[[United Kingdom Census 2001]]|accessdate=2008-12-20}}</ref> Of those aged 16<U+2013>74, 35.6&nbsp;per&nbsp;cent had no [[Education in England#Qualifications|academic qualifications]].<ref>{{citation |title=KS13 Qualifications and students: Census 2001, Key Statistics for urban areas |publisher=statistics.gov.uk |url=http://www.statistics.gov.uk/statbase/ssdataset.asp?vlnk=8326&More=Y|date=2005-02-02|author=Office for National Statistics|authorlink=Office for National Statistics|work=[[United Kingdom Census 2001]]|accessdate=2008-08-05}}</ref>

As of the 2001 UK census, 81.1&nbsp;per&nbsp;cent of Chadderton's residents reported themselves as being Christian, 3.2&nbsp;per&nbsp;cent Muslim, 0.5&nbsp;per&nbsp;cent Hindu, 0.1&nbsp;per&nbsp;cent Buddhist, and 0.1&nbsp;per&nbsp;cent Sikh. The census recorded 8.7&nbsp;per&nbsp;cent as having no religion, 0.1&nbsp;per&nbsp;cent had an alternative religion and 6.3&nbsp;per&nbsp;cent did not state their religion.<ref>{{citation |title=KS07 Religion: Census 2001, Key Statistics for urban areas |publisher=statistics.gov.uk |url=http://www.statistics.gov.uk/statbase/ssdataset.asp?vlnk=8286&More=Y |date=2005-02-02|author=Office for National Statistics|authorlink=Office for National Statistics|work=[[United Kingdom Census 2001]]|accessdate=2008-12-20}}</ref>

Chadderton's population has been described as broadly [[working class]] with pockets of [[lower middle class]] communities, particularly in the northeast of the town, near the border with [[Royton]].<ref>{{Harvnb|Criddle|2002|p=602}}.</ref> Parts of the town are relatively affluent compared to the wider Metropolitan Borough of Oldham.<ref name="Oldham Beyond">{{citation |url=http://www.oldham.gov.uk/oldham_beyond_vision.pdf|format=PDF|title=Oldham Beyond; A Vision for the Borough of Oldham|date=April 2004|accessdate=2008-12-24|publisher=Oldham.gov.uk|author=Urbanism, Environment and Design (URBED)}}</ref>

